 wishing to become familiar with a wide range of such writings in France and England during this period. It will also appeal to researchers interested in Catholic literary and intellectual history in France and England, theologians, philosophers and students of the sociology of religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCatholic writings.  aCharles Péguy.  aG. K. Chesterton.  aGerard Manley Hopkins.  aJ. K. Huysmans.  aLionel Johnson.  aPaul Claudel.  aliterary revivals.  amodernity.  asecularism.1 aSudlow, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779408640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847794086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847794086/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles